Revision history for Perl extension Mail::AutoReply.
1.04  Mon Jun  9 14:58:22 PDT 2008
	- patch from Pascal Gloor to improve bounce detection.

1.02  Sat May 27 23:06:25 PDT 2006
	- fixed URLs in default response text. Thanks: David Ljung Madison

1.01  Tue Jan 18 08:19:19 PST 2005
	- small POD fix for 'send_method_args'

1.00  Mon Jan 17 23:02:12 PST 2005
	- added 'send_method_args' field for modifying arguments passed
	  to sendmail (or whatever send_method is used) to fix
	  rt.cpan.org ticket #9205. Feature suggested by Sean T. Allen.
	- POD updates

0.06  Tue Dec 28 10:58:30 PST 2004
	- updated patterns of addresses *never* sent autoreplies
	- POD and comment updates

0.05  Sat Oct 16 17:04:55 PDT 2004
	- allow easy creation of From address for autoreply using new
	  attributes from_realname and from_email (see POD)
	- removed 'user' attribute
	- fixed bug in creation of From address for autoreply
	- Email::AutoReply is now in Public Beta release

0.04  Wed Aug 25 08:39:55 PDT 2004
	- more minor POD clean-ups. Try to encourage users to read
	Email::AutoReply::DB instead of implementing classes' POD

0.03  Wed Aug 25 08:39:55 PDT 2004
	- major POD clean-up

0.02  Tue Aug 24 19:27:58 PDT 2004
	- first CPAN release

0.01  Sat Aug 14 17:32:49 2004
	- original version; created by h2xs 1.23 with options
		-AX -n Mail::AutoReply


